er bags.  She found a clean silk purple chamise and slid it over her small, but strong frame.  She then grabbed her golden belt and smiled at it.  It was the precious gift given to her from her father, Ares.  She then fastened it around her waist.  She never parted with that precious gift.  Then her hands pulled out her long burgandy Queen's robe and put it on.  Pushing her bags off the chair, she pulled her boots back on.  She picked her bag up and found the golden comb that Ahprodite had given her.  Then she went to the mirror beside the water basin.  Her strong hands pulled the comb thru her wild and careless auburn hair.  When finished she looked herself over and smiled.  Nowing that no matter how clean she was.. she would still be that wild amazon from far away.. she smirked proudly.  And then looked to the door.. wondering how Sethra was doing:::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Sethra</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(7/31/00 7:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Inn</span><hr size=1> :: Sehtra, apon intering the room, found the basin and cleaned herself. She put fresh clothes on and washed the other ones and hung them to dry over the basin. She still had a knife with her but felt weird and untrusting letting a man sharpen her sword. She didn't like to be with out it.<br>
 She noticed a beautiful bed and pillow and immediatly went to it. She laid on the bed, enjoying the softness. Much better than sleeping on tree roots and damp soil.<br>
 She thought about everthing that has happened and then thought about what was to happen later. She noticed a window on the wall and got up to look out. It was a very pretty view. It over looked the the whole Isle. The sky was turning a bright purple,evening was approaching. A few birds flew in the air.<br>
 She went back to the bed and decided to take a quick nap, she was very tired from the journey.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(7/31/00 1:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> warrior in a world far from home</span><hr size=1> :::the amazon queen walked out the door, passing Sethra's room and down the stairs of the inn.  She had decided to give the tired warrior a break.  Stepping out of the inn.. her brown eyes looked about the calming street that night had begun to touch.  She watches as a street light man came by and lit the lamps.  She watched in almost fascinated as he calmly walked along the street lighting the candles in the little glass houseing.  Then the sound of horses pulled her eyes from the silent man.  She turned and walked down to the smithy's barn. The warrior woman catching the odd glance from the inhabitants of the town. As she turned and pushed open the barn door ..she smiled to see Monsoon looking up at her.  Seening the grey mare's big eyes and soft muzzle made Hippolyte feel a little bit of home.  She walked over and hugged the mare around the neck..and then kissed her on the cheek.:: how are you doing old girl? <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 7/31/00 1:23:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Danny OReilly</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/1/00 1