The horses were tired, but strong and well-cared for. He fed and watered them, then dressed their hooves , giving them careful inspection. They'd travelled a long way, but without injury. The blades were much the same; having seen some miles, by the slight telltale  nicks and scratches, but sharper than any he'd care to meet in battle. He chuckled, surmising from these conditions, that the ladies were probably not at ease without their swords within reach. He polished out the scratches, lightly oiled the blades, then gathered them up to return just as the queen entered. She moved with a stealthy grace, her well-muscled form not at all disguised by the royal purple silks, as she moved toward her horse. He couldn't help but stop and admire the goldwork that belted her narrow waist as she reached to embrace the horse, who greeted her with enthusiasm. With a rustle of the weaponry in his arms,<br>
he stepped into the beam of light streaming in through the large side doors that led out from the small stables, catching an almost wild look in her dark brown eyes as she turned::<br>
  &quot; Your mounts and weapons have been seen to, Majesty&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/2/00 8:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Queen, the Smith, and the Barn</span><hr size=1> ::Hippolyte had been so much in her own world, that she had not heard the smithy.  She looked quickly at him as she heard the clank of the weapons he carried.  Recognizing him she quickly calmed.  She smiled quickly as she saw her familiar scimitar, a gift from the Goddess Artemis.:: Efharisto. ::the queen quickly walked over and took the weapon from him.  Then seeing the confusion in his face over her language..she smiled at him:: I mean thank you. :: her brown eyes roamed over the blade of the scimitar and her smile grew:: She looks wonderful!  You have quit the touch with metal!  ::she held the scimitar up ...and then quickly she flicked it around her right side.. then slashed low before her.. her eyes and smile wild.. as if seeing a foe before her.::: She is a glorious isn't she?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Danny OReilly</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/3/00 11:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> in the presence of the  Queen</span><hr size=1> :: Her catlike grace and lightning speed, undiminished by the long journey, surprised him into taking a step back as she cut the air. For a moment, she looked as if she'd slay him in his boots right where he stood, but it past quickly and he exhaled a breath in relief::<br>
&quot; Aye, majesty, she's a glorious work, and a pleasure<br>
for these 'ands to 'ave held..no need to thank me, tis an honor..&quot;<br>
::he glanced from her wild smile to the flashing scimitar::  <br>
&quot;..I didnae effect her bite, still sharp as a winter morn, just gave 'er a little spruce up..&quot;<br>
::He nodded respectfully, then stepped inside and indicated a door opening at the back of the stable with a jerk of his head::<br>
 &quot;..all yer tack an gear is stowed there, and th' old gal here 'as had hay and honeyed oats, and more water than's needed ta float a rowboat..&quot;<br>
:: He chuckled , then moved slowly back toward the double doors that led out::<br>
&quot;It's nice ta see visitors from far away, mayhaps we'll 'ave a chance tae chat over a meal at the tavern sometime while yer 'ere...if there be anythin else yer needin, just make yer requests known, Highness..&quot;<br>
